FBIS4-4120 "drchi082_o_94002" FBIS-CHI-94-082 Daily Report 27 Apr 1994 REGIONAL AFFAIRS East Region Anhui Blast Furnace Begins Operation Anhui Blast Furnace Begins Operation OW2704035794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0305 GMT 27 Apr 94 OW2704035794 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Beijing, April 27 (XINHUA)--A 2,500-cu-m [cubic meter] blast furnace went into operation Tuesday [26 April] afternoon at the Maanshan Iron and Steel Co. Ltd, one of the country's major iron and steel producers, in east China's Anhui Province. At 3:18 P.M. on Tuesday, the furnace successfully produced molten iron. The total investment in the furnace reached three billion yuan (about 345 million U.S. dollars). The designed annual output of the furnace is 1.75 million tons. With this furnace in production, the company will be able to double its annual output to four million tons of iron and steel. This also paves the way for it to increase its annual output to six million tons of iron and steel.
